Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.97,0:00:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has the patient's condition changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.73,0:00:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.44,0:00:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's his blood pressure and pulse rate?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.31,0:00:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.07,0:00:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Mayor Roedecker's operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.48,0:00:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm beginning the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.99,0:00:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.70,0:00:33.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah. What's the patient's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.41,0:00:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.08,0:00:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this boy's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.20,0:00:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.91,0:00:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't... know his name, do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.88,0:00:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.21,0:00:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.80,0:00:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.74,0:00:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill... him...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.13,0:01:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill... him...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.62,0:01:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.16,0:01:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The twins! I can't find them anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.04,0:01:27.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really look everywhere?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.71,0:01:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.88,0:01:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I looked everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.80,0:01:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're playing hide and seek somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:49.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Maybe they're playing hide and seek somewhere," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.78,0:02:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scaredy-cat Tenma! Scaredy-cat Tenma! Yaaay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.58,0:02:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use hiding, scaredy-cat Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you force yourself to hide, \N you'll wet your pants again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.05,0:03:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys, it s getting late! How much\Nlonger are you going to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.56,0:03:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.89,0:03:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.10,0:03:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.02,0:03:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.86,0:03:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.70,0:03:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.29,0:03:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come find me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.30,0:03:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.18,0:03:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come find me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.81,0:03:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Scaredy-cat Tenma," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.43,0:05:28.72,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,200)\pos(368,351)}A Monster of Chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.17,0:05:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.21,0:05:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man who came earlier this evening\Nis still waiting at the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.09,0:05:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the psychiatrist of Richard\NBraun, that detective we hired.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.77,0:05:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get rid of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.02,0:05:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karl, I can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.15,0:05:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of man is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.86,0:05:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's an older man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.36,0:06:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.78,0:06:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't look like a bad man...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.16,0:06:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he looks like he's at his wit's end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.10,0:06:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.84,0:06:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for seeing me, Herr Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.72,0:06:31.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's skip the pleasantries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.48,0:06:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.31,0:06:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let me hear what you have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have much time, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.65,0:06:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how long this takes depends entirely on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.03,0:06:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you come to ask about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.16,0:06:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.29,0:06:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'm right, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.88,0:07:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suspected someone like you would\Ncome to see me someday...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.55,0:07:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to solve the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.43,0:07:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.93,0:07:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's too perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.35,0:07:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People who can see may not \N understand this, but I feel it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.03,0:07:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a man who is in perfect harmony with himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.03,0:07:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's as though he doesn't really exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.74,0:07:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He does exist, I assure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.58,0:07:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, I've gathered fragments of his past.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.79,0:07:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll read it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.54,0:07:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll find that he is neither a \N phantom nor an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.55,0:07:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The story begins in 1986, when a fatally \N wounded boy was carried into a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.90,0:08:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, he appeared before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.03,0:08:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the late... no, murdered Richard...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.53,0:08:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan had a student named Fahren\Npretend to be your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.96,0:08:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, as soon as your real son Karl appeared, he\Nchanged his plans and helped reunite the two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.55,0:08:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Fahren committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.10,0:08:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you come to accept your son,\Nwho was apart from you for so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In these last few years, how many\Npeople close to you have died?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.65,0:08:47.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The driver who served you for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The maid who read books to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.57,0:08:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The accountant who had been your\Nbird-watching companion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.24,0:08:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.45,0:08:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything happened because\NJohan wanted to isolate you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.41,0:09:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he could get to your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.67,0:09:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, help me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything must be brought to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.09,0:09:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, the Japanese doctor, Dr. Tenma...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.14,0:09:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said Johan was playing with people as\Nthough they were ants in a line, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ants in a line...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.57,0:09:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what people call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Vampire of Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.25,0:09:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accepted the nickname with pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.92,0:09:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I try to master myself, somehow\Nit gets bigger and bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.18,0:09:55.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster inside of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.31,0:10:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.23,0:10:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The nickname sounds great, but I'm so feeble.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.40,0:10:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I also wanted to play as\Nthough I was toying with a line of ants...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.90,0:10:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.28,0:10:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to become what I wanted to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.16,0:10:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Who is like unto the Monster?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.08,0:10:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Who is able to make war with him?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.72,0:10:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Johan's revelation?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.30,0:10:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think only a greater monster can defeat this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.87,0:11:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you guys discussing? \N It's morning already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.63,0:11:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, where is Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.46,0:11:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's heading to the ceremony hall directly\Nfrom the Ester Hohen office.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.80,0:11:23.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look very tired. Should I \N cancel today"s ceremony?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, get me ready for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.73,0:11:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill... him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.07,0:11:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.74,0:11:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.57,0:11:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only performed your duty as a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.82,0:11:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.49,0:11:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.66,0:12:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And... please save as many lives as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.34,0:12:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.82,0:12:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.70,0:12:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really going to quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.83,0:12:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just started to get used to the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.83,0:12:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.41,0:12:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come see me if you're ever back in the area, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.50,0:12:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will. Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.97,0:12:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was a good girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.01,0:12:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Is Lotte Frank there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.14,0:12:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lotte is out right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.93,0:13:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Could you tell her that I'm taking\Na train out of Munich at three?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.69,0:13:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.61,0:13:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, may I have your name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.65,0:13:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.61,0:13:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.02,0:13:40.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.02,0:13:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His car just pulled up at the back entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.69,0:13:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Vampire of Bayern is finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.90,0:13:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shhh. He 'II hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.94,0:13:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see the guests in the hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.45,0:13:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, not just from Bayern, but company representatives\Nfrom all over Europe, America and Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.28,0:14:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and so many ambassadors and politicians...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.25,0:14:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that this is just a donation\Nceremony for a collection of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.92,0:14:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They say that every single thing Mr. Schuwald\Ndoes affects the whole European economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.05,0:14:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He rarely shows up in public, so\Neveryone came to see, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.55,0:14:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's suddenly donating his library now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's like he's giving away his last will and testament.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.35,0:14:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.06,0:14:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a vital person to the European economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.65,0:14:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need him to stay alive a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.36,0:14:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.82,0:14:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.16,0:14:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot a document. Can you go get it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.45,0:14:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What document?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.37,0:14:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just go back and get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.79,0:14:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's on the desk in my study.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.92,0:14:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.79,0:14:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan is coming soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.84,0:14:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll take care of everything here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.70,0:15:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening with the investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.74,0:15:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.74,0:15:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.29,0:15:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were going to \N put a lot of effort into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.75,0:15:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I told you Tenma was in Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.67,0:15:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.84,0:15:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you check up on Johan Liebert, who is\Nworking as Schuwald s secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.76,0:15:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no mistake that he's the real serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.26,0:15:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.64,0:15:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hurry, Tenma may...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.26,0:15:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma is trying to settle this on his own!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.94,0:15:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. The investigation is going quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.86,0:16:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.07,0:16:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan is right in front of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.62,0:16:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, arrest him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.62,0:16:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are indeed a criminal psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good way to put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.75,0:16:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, Johan does exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.05,0:16:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan exists...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,inside Tenma's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.81,0:16:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get anything new out of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.10,0:16:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.65,0:16:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been saying the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.07,0:16:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gun was a Mauser SR-93.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.11,0:16:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person he sold it to was Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.49,0:16:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we question him some more?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.83,0:16:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's probably all he knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.08,0:16:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.41,0:16:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mauser SR-93 is a sniper rifle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.29,0:16:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's a quality model.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.13,0:16:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who the target is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.51,0:17:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.97,0:17:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1 am Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.27,0:17:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I procured a high-grade sniper rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.36,0:17:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.44,0:17:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.82,0:17:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.45,0:17:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who would I shoot with this rifle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.74,0:17:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed the hospital directors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.25,0:17:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I killed several middle-aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.67,0:17:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now who should I kill?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.30,0:17:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.38,0:17:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should eat something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.45,0:18:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.41,0:18:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.25,0:18:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine, don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.46,0:18:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.51,0:18:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1 may not look like it now, but when I was a cop and\Na doctor for the National Border Security Patrol...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.01,0:18:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was well-trained, both physically and psychologically.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.22,0:18:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will definitely save your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.10,0:18:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.31,0:18:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate an ex-police doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.82,0:18:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you kindly prepared breakfast\Nfor me, so I'm going to eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.03,0:18:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't fight on an empty stomach, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.26,0:19:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.80,0:19:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You found something?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schuwald's library donation ceremony!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:14.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.39,0:19:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dieter, wait here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.94,0:19:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.53,0:19:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Schuwald!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.24,0:19:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.61,0:19:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see Hans Georg Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.49,0:19:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.74,0:19:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.74,0:19:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh I think he's at the Munich University library\Ndonating his collection of books today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.08,0:19:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go there immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.67,0:19:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.25,0:19:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma's target is Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.76,0:19:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, please welcome Mr. Hans Georg Schuwald, who\Ngave us this huge and precious collection of books.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.11,0:20:08.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.78,0:20:10.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is my secretary here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.99,0:20:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.99,0:20:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he's right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.26,0:20:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.07,0:20:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought him back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.00,0:21:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... brought that monster back to life...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.09,0:21:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.26,0:21:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.39,0:21:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.68,0:21:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I looked for him everywhere,\Nbut he doesn't seem to be here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.94,0:21:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though we've become friends, it's too bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.48,0:21:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.99,0:21:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are twins, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.03,0:21:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.24,0:21:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.41,0:21:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does this picture book mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.41,0:21:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He suddenly collapsed when he saw this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.33,0:21:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A picture book?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.02,0:22:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,229)}Kill... him...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.88,0:22:31.05,Lyrics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(175,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:44.48,Lyrics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(188,474)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:44.48,Lyrics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(193,23)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.48,0:22:47.44,Lyrics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.44,0:23:01.12,Lyrics,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(188,474)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes.
